overview: The user initiated a request to enhance the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire application, feeling it lacked visual appeal. The agent began by
  conducting a comprehensive review of the existing styling, identifying areas
  such as the generic color palette, plain backgrounds, and basic form elements.
  A new sleep-themed color palette was introduced, along with custom utility
  classes for gradients and shadows. The main form layout was redesigned with
  subtle decorative elements and an improved progress indicator. Key UI
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards received
  significant styling updates. The welcome (Intro) section was transformed with
  a hero element and feature cards. All questionnaire sections were updated to
  use the new consistent styling, replacing old gray boxes with more refined
  card-like groupings. A console error related to  values in input fields
  was also identified and fixed by modifying the  component to safely
  handle  values. After an initial review, the user pointed out remaining
  inconsistencies in the Report section's colors, which the agent is now
  addressing, along with further refining alert colors and border opacities
  across the app.
